title: American nurse and her child are kidnapped in Haiti, nonprofit says
description: The woman, Alix Dorsainvil, 31, is from New Hampshire but lives in Haiti and is married to the organization’s director, Sandro Dorsainvil.

title: Blinken says U.S. aid to Niger in ‘clear jeopardy’ after military coup
description: Washington is poised to cut off humanitarian assistance to Niger if its democratically elected leader is not restored to office, Secretary of State Antony Blinken said.

title: U.S. to provide up to $345 million in military aid to Taiwan
description: It marks the first time the Presidential Drawdown Authority, which pulls directly from U.S. stockpiles, has been used for Taiwan. It has been used before for Ukraine.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Dnipro strike injures 9; Brazil rejects U.S. request for alleged Russian spy
description: A Russian missile strike on the Ukrainian city of Dnipro on Friday evening hit a high-rise and a security service building, the regional governor said.

title: 4 missing after helicopter ditches into sea during Australia-U.S. drill
description: The accident paused a large-scale military exercise, as Secretary of State Antony Blinken and Secretary of Defense Lloyd Austin were visiting Australia.

title: In repeat bombing of Odessa, Putin deepens economic war on Ukraine
description: Since terminating a deal that allowed Ukrainian grain exports in the Black Sea, Russia has stepped up attacks on ports, storage facilities and other agricultural infrastructure.

title: Brazil rejects U.S. extradition request for alleged Russian spy
description: Brazil’s justice minister said Sergey Cherkasov will remain imprisoned in Brazil for the time being.
